---
/**
 * rest-api/0009 · Figure 1 — "anatomy of a problem+json error body": the five
 * RFC 9457 core fields (type/title/status/detail/instance), the extension
 * members you add (code/message/errors), and the never-leak-internals banner.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0009-error-design-rate-limiting-observability.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component because raw inline
 * SVG with kebab-case attributes is unreliable inside MDX but is plain HTML
 * inside .astro. No arrowhead markers here, so no local <defs> is needed.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 620 270"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Anatomy of a problem+json error body: the five RFC 9457 fields type, title, status, detail, instance, plus extension members code, message, and field-level errors"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="310"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110"
                >ANATOMY OF A <tspan font-family="ui-monospace,monospace">problem+json</tspan> ERROR BODY</text
            >
            <text x="310" y="34" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >Content-Type: application/problem+json · RFC 9457 (supersedes 7807)</text
            >
            <rect x="14" y="44" width="592" height="214" rx="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <!-- RFC 9457 core five -->
            <rect x="28" y="58" width="290" height="124" rx="7" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="40" y="74" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
                >RFC 9457 CORE FIELDS</text
            >
            <text x="40" y="94" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace,monospace" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >"type"</text
            >
            <text x="120" y="94" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">URI naming the problem class</text>
            <text x="40" y="112" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace,monospace" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >"title"</text
            >
            <text x="120" y="112" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">short human summary</text>
            <text x="40" y="130" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace,monospace" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >"status"</text
            >
            <text x="120" y="130" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">HTTP code, e.g. 422</text>
            <text x="40" y="148" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace,monospace" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >"detail"</text
            >
            <text x="120" y="148" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">this-occurrence explanation</text>
            <text x="40" y="166" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace,monospace" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >"instance"</text
            >
            <text x="120" y="166" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">URI of this specific event</text>
            <!-- extension members -->
            <rect x="330" y="58" width="262" height="124" rx="7" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text x="342" y="74" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >EXTENSION MEMBERS (you add)</text
            >
            <text x="342" y="94" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace,monospace" fill="#7a1f12"
                >"code"</text
            >
            <text x="430" y="94" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e">stable, clients branch on it</text>
            <text x="342" y="112" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >e.g. "card_declined" — never the title string</text
            >
            <text x="342" y="132" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace,monospace" fill="#7a1f12"
                >"message"</text
            >
            <text x="430" y="132" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">human, for logs/devs</text>
            <text x="342" y="152" font-size="10" font-family="ui-monospace,monospace" fill="#7a1f12"
                >"errors"</text
            >
            <text x="430" y="152" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">field-level validation list</text>
            <text x="342" y="170" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">which field failed, and why</text>
            <!-- never leak banner -->
            <rect
                x="28"
                y="194"
                width="564"
                height="50"
                rx="7"
                fill="#fff"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-dasharray="4 3"></rect>
            <text x="44" y="214" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
                >✗ NEVER LEAK INTERNALS</text
            >
            <text x="44" y="232" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >no stack traces · no SQL fragments · no internal ids · no "which layer failed" —
                that is reconnaissance for an attacker.</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Clients branch on a <strong>stable <code>code</code></strong>, humans read the <code
            >title</code
        >/<code>message</code>, and <code>errors[]</code> says <em>which field</em> failed — all under
        one media type.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
